'''T-Palette Records''' is a [[Japan]]ese [[record label]], specializing in [[Japanese idol|idols]]. It is a subsidiary of the [[Tower Records#Japan|Japanese franchise of Tower Records]].<ref name="billboardjapan20121211" />

== History ==
The record label was launched in June 2011.<ref name="zakzak20111108">{{cite news|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111110142106/http://www.zakzak.co.jp/zakspa/news/20111108/zsp1111081401004-n1.htm|url=http://www.zakzak.co.jp/zakspa/news/20111108/zsp1111081401004-n1.htm|script-title=ja:タワーレコード社長が語る“ご当地アイドル”の可能性|publisher=[[Zakzak]]|date=2011-11-08|archivedate=2011-11-10|accessdate=2014-05-03|language=Japanese}}</ref>

The first artist of the new label, [[Vanilla Beans (band)|Vanilla Beans]], was rented to it by [[Tokuma Japan Communications]]. Such an unusual case when an artist was transferred from one record label to another on rent, attracted attention in the media.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.news24.jp/entertainment/news/1617601.html |title=バニラビーンズ、前代未聞のレンタル移籍! |newspaper=日テレNEWS24 |date=2011-06-03|accessdate=2011-11-19 |publisher=日本テレビ放送網}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://news.livedoor.com/article/detail/5610025/ |title=タワレコ発のアイドル専門レーベルにバニラビーンズがレンタル移籍（Girls News） |newspaper=Livedoor News|date=2011-06-04|accessdate=2011-11-19|publisher=Livedoor}}</ref>。

